\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}4 bone-in chicken thigh and leg or chicken breasts\
{\listtext	\'95	}Salt and freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons poultry seasoning\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grill/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grill}} seasoning\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 thick cut slices {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pancetta/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pancetta}} or bacon, chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 medium red onion, chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cloves {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garlic}}, grated or finely chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 to 2 sprigs fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rosemary/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 rosemary}}, finely chopped\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup balsamic vinegar\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons brown sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/worcestershire-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Worcestershire sauce}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup tomato sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 1/2 cups chicken stock\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 cups milk\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup quick cooking polenta\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/butter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 butter}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup grated Parmiginao-Reggiano\
{\listtext	\'95	}Torn fresh basil leaves\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.\
Season the chicken liberally with salt and pepper, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/poultry/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 poultry}} seasoning, and grill seasoning. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a medium skillet and brown the chicken a few minutes on each side to put some of it's flavor and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/drippings/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 drippings}} into the pan then transfer to oven and roast 15 minutes more or until juices run clear. Meanwhile, add 1 more tablespoon olive oil to the pan and cook pancetta or bacon, if using, until {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crisp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 crisp}}. Add onions, garlic and rosemary, cook 5 minutes then add the vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire, tomato sauce and 1/2 cup {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/stock/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chicken stock}}, reduce heat to low and let sauce {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simmer}} 5 minutes more.\
Bring remaining 1 1/2 cups stock and milk to a boil, whisk in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/polenta/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 polenta}} and season with salt and pepper. Whisk polenta 2 to 3 minutes until it thickens, stir in butter and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cheese/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cheese}}, remove from heat.\
Remove chicken from oven and turn in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/barbecue-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 barbecue sauce}}. Fill shallow bowls with polenta Top with chicken, spoon extra sauce over chicken and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garnish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garnish}} with some torn basil leaves.\
